                            <comment id="18528" author="robh" created="Tue, 11 Jul 2006 20:11:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is an interesting question. Without doubt the new model is more correct but I can see the argument that the older approach is much nicer from a programmatic point of view. I&apos;ll see what the other guys think about this and see if we can reach some consensus.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18541" author="joshmoore" created="Wed, 12 Jul 2006 02:04:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On the devel list there was a thread regarding this issue. Matt saw code changes 1-&amp;gt;2 as ok, but context changes as less so. For multiple interfaces, however, this did break the xml. Previously I configured a proxy for two interfaces as such:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &amp;lt;bean id=&quot;queryService&quot; parent=&quot;managedService&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property name=&quot;proxyInterfaces&quot; value=&quot;ome.api.IQuery,ome.api.local.LocalQuery&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property name=&quot;target&quot; ref=&quot;ome.api.IQuery&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/bean&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and after the change it required this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &amp;lt;bean id=&quot;queryService&quot; parent=&quot;managedService&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property name=&quot;proxyInterfaces&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;ome.api.IQuery&amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;ome.api.local.LocalQuery&amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;/list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property name=&quot;target&quot; ref=&quot;ome.api.IQuery&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/bean&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Perhaps I missed something in the migration docs about needing a new PropertyEditor, but this seemed a substantial switch to me.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Josh.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18626" author="robh" created="Mon, 17 Jul 2006 02:55:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We decided to keep this property as Class[]. I also added a ClassArrayEditor which is configured by default so that the original comma-separated list style should continue to work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rob&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
